OL,3,CIs the UK any nearer to making
OL,4,Cassisted dying legal?
OL,6,FThe NHS describes euthanasia as "the
OL,7,Fact of deliberately ending a person's
OL,8,Flife to relieve suffering".
OL,10,FAssisted suicide meanwhile is "the act
OL,11,Fof deliberately assisting another
OL,12,Fperson to kill themselves".
OL,14,FIs it legal in the UK?
OL,16,FBoth euthanasia and assisted suicide
OL,17,Fare illegal under current English and
OL,18,FWelsh law.
