OL,3,CIs the UK any nearer to making
OL,4,Cassisted dying legal?
OL,6,FThere are strong arguments on both
OL,7,Fsides of the debate in terms of
OL,8,Fwhether assisted dying should be
OL,9,Flegalised.
OL,11,FThe charity Humanists UK is among the
OL,12,Fgroups that fully support assisted
OL,13,Fdying, as it explains in a policy on
OL,14,Fits website:
OL,16,F"We believe that any adult of sound
OL,17,Fmind who is intolerably suffering from
OL,18,Fan incurable, physical condition and
OL,19,Fhas a clear and settled wish to die
OL,20,Fshould have the option of an assisted
OL,21,Fdeath."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G8/15
