OL,3,CIs the UK any nearer to making
OL,4,Cassisted dying legal?
OL,6,FIt states that the right to die in the
OL,7,Fway a person chooses should be "a
OL,8,Ffundamental human right".
OL,10,FThe charity gives the following list
OL,11,Fof reasons as to why assisted dying
OL,12,Fshould be legalised across the UK:
OL,14,F"Families are often forced to make an
OL,15,Fintolerable choice between either
OL,16,Fletting their loved ones suffer, or
OL,17,Fsupporting them to travel abroad and
OL,18,Frisking criminal investigation," the
OL,19,Fcharity says, referring to more than
OL,20,F200 UK citizens who have travelled
OL,21,Fabroad to end their lives since 2015.
